The paper deals with image data and proposes a technique for detecting damages in civil engineering structures. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for recognizing bridge structural and non-structural components from images of urban scenes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the integration of scene understanding with component recognition, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of CNNs also suggests the involvement of machine learning (ML) techniques, which could place the paper in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the reduction of false-positives, which could place it in the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves the detection and localization of critical structural components, which could place it in the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
